Ri referred to a joint statement issued by Kim Jong Un and Donald Trump at the first summit between a seated US president and a North Korean leader in Singapore on 12 June, where Kim promised to work towards "the decommissioning of nuclear weapons on the Korean peninsula" while Trump promised guarantees for North Korea's security.
North Korea has sought a formal end to the Korean War 1950-53, but the United States has said that Pyongyang must first phase out its nuclear weapons.
Washington has also turned down negotiations to ease severe international sanctions against North Korea.
"USA insists on "decommissioning first" and increases pressure through sanctions to achieve its purpose through coercion and even opposes the "declaration of ending the war," says Ri.
"The notion that sanctions can get us on our knees is a wishful dream for those people who lack knowledge about us.
